<h5><img alt="3 ballroom couples" height="384" src="Images/dance/Ballroom 3 couples.jpg" width="652" /></h5>
<h3>Dance Internships</h3>
<hr />
<h4>Students must be registered for Dance internships BEFORE the third week of school.</h4>
<h4>Past experience will generally not be counted towards an internship. Internships are not required for the Dance Major, but are <strong>strongly encouraged</strong>.</h4>
<h4>The <a href="Documents/dance/DA498.pdf" title="DA 498 Course Syllabus">DA 498 Course Syllabus</a> has more information about Dance Internships.</h4>
<h4>For additional information on internships, please visit with the Internship Coordinator, <a href="x27982.xml">James Gordon</a>, phone mumber: 496-9875, Office: MC 377A.</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h5>All internships must be pre-approved and registered for before the student begins the internship experience. The student is responsible to:</h5>
<ul>
<li>
<h5>Complete the necessary prerequisites for the internship experience.</h5>
</li>
<li>
<h5>Find an internship/job opportunity.</h5>
</li>
<li>
<h5>Go to <a href="http://www.byui.edu/careerservices">www.byui.edu/careerservices</a> and complete the Initial Internship Approval form.</h5>
</li>
<li>
<h5>Take the completed Initial Internship Approval form to KIM 230 with any other necessary documentation.</h5>
</li>
<li>
<h5>Ensure employer/internship provider registers online and signs the Master Internship Agreement with BYU-Idaho.</h5>
</li>
<li>
<h5>When the internship is approved, the BYU-Idaho Internship Office will register the student for the internship.</h5>
</li>
</ul>
